<span id="ix.ii.xv-p2"></span> This sentence has completely baffled all
the critics. \[Its banter, or mock gravity, has not been self-evident.\]
We cannot enter upon the wide field of discussion which it has opened
up, but would simply state that Irenæus here seems to us, as often, to
be playing upon the terms which were in common use among these heretics.
Marcus probably received his system from Colorbasus, and is here
declared, by the use of that jargon which Irenæus means to ridicule
while so employing it, to have proceeded to develop it in the way
described.

